{
  "name": "Combat Insight",
  "type": "basicAction",
  "img": "icons/svg/light.svg",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p ><span >You can spend <strong >1 AP</strong> to attempt to discern the course of actions a creature might take on its next turn. </span></p><p ><span >Make an <strong >Insight </strong><strong>Check</strong> contested by the target’s <strong >Trickery </strong>or <strong >Influence </strong><strong>Check</strong> (its choice).</span></p><p ><span ><strong >Success:</strong> You learn the target’s emotional state and whether it plans to make an Attack, cast a Spell, or flee combat during its next turn. </span></p><p ><span ><strong >Success (5):</strong> You know who the creature is likely to target with a harmful ability. </span></p><p ><span ><strong >Success (10):</strong> You know which ability the creature plans to use.</span></p><p></p><p><span ><em>If the target is a PC, its player tells you what the creature plans to do. If the target is an NPC, the GM tells you what the creature plans to do.</em></span></p>",
